[
    {
        "content": "<p>Hello guys.<br>\nIf I define raw kernel module with kernel::prelude::module! and implement method init in kernel::Module for SampleDriver, how can I create pinned variable on heap using KBox maybe, so it will not be destroyed when init is done. I would like to delete it manually in drop() for this SampleDriver.</p>",
        "id": 526841392,
        "sender_full_name": "Igor Korotin",
        "timestamp": 1751474093
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>When you said \"global\", you meant \"global\" to your module, right? I.e the variable should only be accessible within the module. If so I think you can put it in your module struct:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"cp\">#[pin_data]</span>\n<span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">struct</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">MyModule</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"cp\">#[pin]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">data</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Foo</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"c1\">// ^ usually it's a `driver::Registration&lt;&gt;` so that all the driver</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"c1\">// callbacks of the same driver can access it.</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">InPlaceModule</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">MyModule</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">..</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 526850994,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1751477919
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I just need to save ARef&lt;i2c::DeviceOwned&gt; object that I created in init(). The code:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">struct</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">DriverModule</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">pdev</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">ARef</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">i2c</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">DeviceOwned</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">const</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">BOARD_INFO</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">i2c</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">I2cBoardInfo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">i2c</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">I2cBoardInfo</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">new</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">c_str</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s\">\"rust_device_i2c\"</span><span class=\"p\">),</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mh\">0x30</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">Module</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">DriverModule</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">init</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">_module</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"o\">'</span><span class=\"nb\">static</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">ThisModule</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Result</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">pr_info</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s\">\"DriverModule on</span><span class=\"se\">\\n</span><span class=\"s\">\"</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">adapter</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">i2c</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">I2cAdapter</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">get</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">).</span><span class=\"n\">ok_or</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">EINVAL</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"o\">?</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">device</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">i2c</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">DeviceOwned</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">Core</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">new</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"n\">adapter</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"n\">BOARD_INFO</span><span class=\"p\">).</span><span class=\"n\">ok_or</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">EINVAL</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"o\">?</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">deviceowned</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">ARef</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">i2c</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">DeviceOwned</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"n\">device</span><span class=\"p\">).</span><span class=\"n\">into</span><span class=\"p\">();</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">mem</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">KBox</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">new</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">deviceowned</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">GFP_KERNEL</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"o\">?</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"nb\">Ok</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"n\">pdev</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Box</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">alloc</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">allocator</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">Kmalloc</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">into_inner</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">mem</span><span class=\"p\">)})</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Drop</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">DriverModule</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">drop</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">pr_info</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s\">\"DriverModule off</span><span class=\"se\">\\n</span><span class=\"s\">\"</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">kernel</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">prelude</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">module</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">type</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"nc\">DriverModule</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">name</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"s\">\"rust_test\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">authors</span><span class=\"p\">:[</span><span class=\"s\">\"Igor Korotin\"</span><span class=\"p\">],</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">description</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"s\">\"Rust test\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">license</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"s\">\"GPL v2\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>when running this code I get the following:<br>\n[   14.998432] rust_test: DriverModule on<br>\n[   15.000436] rust_kernel: inc_ref  <br>\n[   15.001943] rust_kernel: as_ref<br>\n[   15.003607] rust_kernel: drop DeviceOwned                <strong>&lt;&lt; but after init ends, I see that my object is destroyed</strong> <br>\n[   15.005097] rust_kernel: as_raw_client</p>\n<p>What am I missing?</p>",
        "id": 526961745,
        "sender_full_name": "Igor Korotin",
        "timestamp": 1751537252
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You need to box it?</p>",
        "id": 526962002,
        "sender_full_name": "Wren T",
        "timestamp": 1751537346
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The goal is to save ARef&lt;DeviceOwned&gt; while the module is loaded. I just don't get how to do that to be honest</p>",
        "id": 526962167,
        "sender_full_name": "Igor Korotin",
        "timestamp": 1751537418
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Okay, so I would think that can't change. Have you looked at pin-init?</p>",
        "id": 526962407,
        "sender_full_name": "Wren T",
        "timestamp": 1751537507
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><a href=\"https://rust-for-linux.com/pin-init\">https://rust-for-linux.com/pin-init</a></p>",
        "id": 526962503,
        "sender_full_name": "Wren T",
        "timestamp": 1751537531
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>No, I'll dig into pin-init then, thanks</p>",
        "id": 526962575,
        "sender_full_name": "Igor Korotin",
        "timestamp": 1751537556
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The value can change. The location change change.</p>",
        "id": 526962590,
        "sender_full_name": "Wren T",
        "timestamp": 1751537561
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'm not typing well. The location cannot change.</p>",
        "id": 526962648,
        "sender_full_name": "Wren T",
        "timestamp": 1751537581
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Look at the rnull_mod device for an example.</p>",
        "id": 526962838,
        "sender_full_name": "Wren T",
        "timestamp": 1751537640
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You will also need to use InPlaceModule instead of Module.</p>",
        "id": 526963030,
        "sender_full_name": "Wren T",
        "timestamp": 1751537699
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Note that <code>ARef&lt;_&gt;</code> is already a pointer to an object, and the object is already pinned.</p>",
        "id": 527065355,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1751572862
    },
    {
        "content": "<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">device</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">i2c</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">DeviceOwned</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">Core</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">new</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"n\">adapter</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"n\">BOARD_INFO</span><span class=\"p\">).</span><span class=\"n\">ok_or</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">EINVAL</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"o\">?</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>What does the <code>new()</code> function do? Seems you create a <code>DeviceOwned</code> on the stack.</p>",
        "id": 527065559,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1751572962
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>and when <code>init()</code> returns, the <code>device</code> goes out of scope and <code>i2c::DeviceOwned</code> gets dropped. Most likely you should not implement the <code>new()</code> to directly return a <code>DeviceOwned</code>.</p>",
        "id": 527066261,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1751573312
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It's easier if you could share all the code.</p>",
        "id": 527066336,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1751573348
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I assume you're using <code>i2c_new_client_device()</code> to implement <code>new()</code>? If so the returned pointer for <code>i2c_new_client_device()</code> already carries one refcount, you can just convert that into a <code>ARef&lt;DeviceOwned&gt;</code> (via <code>ARef::from_raw()</code>), and return (your <code>new()</code> should return a <code>Result&lt;ARef&lt;_&gt;&gt;</code>)</p>",
        "id": 527067760,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1751574099
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"411647\">@Boqun Feng</span> I'm currently implementing I2C subsystem including creation of new I2C device via i2c_new_client_device as you have noticed correctly. The problem was with the correct implementation of DeviceOwned that suppose to carry i2c_client created by i2c_new_client_device and drop it automatically when it leaves the scope. After some additional investigation I think I have implemented the correct behavior of DeviceOwned. <br>\nThe problem was that when I return this DeviceOwned which was (NonNull&lt;i2c::Device&lt;Ctx: device::DeviceContext, state::Owned&gt;&gt;) from new into my module, it was automatically dropped after init because I couldn't save it correctly and was not sure how to do that.</p>",
        "id": 527131537,
        "sender_full_name": "Igor Korotin",
        "timestamp": 1751617605
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>In general I think the problem is solved and this thread can be closed.</p>",
        "id": 527131659,
        "sender_full_name": "Igor Korotin",
        "timestamp": 1751617640
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So your <code>DeviceOwned</code> is another smart pointer that you want it to own a <code>i2c::Device</code>?</p>",
        "id": 527204275,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1751644976
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Generally, that's not a good idea, you should just use <code>ARef&lt;i2c::Device&lt;..&gt;&gt;</code></p>",
        "id": 527204361,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1751645017
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>but maybe you have special requirement in your driver?</p>",
        "id": 527204457,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1751645063
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You're in cc to the patch series<br>\n<a href=\"https://lore.kernel.org/rust-for-linux/20250704153332.1193214-1-igor.korotin.linux@gmail.com/T/#t\">https://lore.kernel.org/rust-for-linux/20250704153332.1193214-1-igor.korotin.linux@gmail.com/T/#t</a></p>",
        "id": 527204471,
        "sender_full_name": "Igor Korotin",
        "timestamp": 1751645073
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Maybe I have implemented that incorrectly, but the idea was basically to automatically delete i2c device that is created by i2c_new_client_device and also to protect \"non-user\" created  devices from deregistration.</p>",
        "id": 527204735,
        "sender_full_name": "Igor Korotin",
        "timestamp": 1751645191
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You have the \"automatically deletion\" via device refcount, no? That is if the <code>put_device()</code>, it'll unregister and free the device.</p>",
        "id": 527205120,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1751645365
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Hmm.. but it seems i2c_client does something special.</p>",
        "id": 527205268,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1751645428
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think the implementation of <code>DeviceOwned</code> is still incorrect, after we call <code>i2c_new_client_device()</code>, the refcount of the device is 1, and in the drop function of <code>DeviceOwned</code> which would call <code>put_device()</code>, that reduces the refcount to 0, and then after <code>DeviceOwned::drop()</code> returns <code>ARef::drop()</code> will be called, that would access the device, but the device should be gone already.</p>",
        "id": 527206171,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1751645753
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Ah, ok, you used <code>.into()</code> in <code>DeviceOwned::new()</code>, and that will make the returned i2c device has refcount=2, so the above case cannot happen.</p>",
        "id": 527207840,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1751646337
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"934292\">Igor Korotin</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/291565-Help/topic/global.20mutable.20variable.20in.20kernel.20module/near/527204735\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Maybe I have implemented that incorrectly, but the idea was basically to automatically delete i2c device that is created by i2c_new_client_device and also to protect \"non-user\" created  devices from deregistration.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>So essientially <code>DeviceOwned</code> is a special refcount that controls <code>i2c_unregister_device()</code> behavior, and it works with other refcounts of the device, and that's good ;-)</p>",
        "id": 527211428,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1751647527
    }
]